      <div class="moon-grid">
        <div class="moon-item">
          <span class="moon-phase">🌑</span>
          <strong>New Moon</strong>
          <p>Maximum darkness. Best conditions for faint aurora, long-exposure photography, and seeing the Milky Way alongside the aurora.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="moon-item">
          <span class="moon-phase">🌓</span>
          <strong>Quarter Moon</strong>
          <p>Acceptable — sets early or rises late. Plan your viewing window around the moon's position. Check moonrise/moonset times for your location.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="moon-item">
          <span class="moon-phase">🌕</span>
          <strong>Full Moon</strong>
          <p>Brightens the sky significantly. Faint aurora (Kp 1–3) may be washed out. Strong displays (Kp 5+) are still visible and can create beautiful moonlit aurora landscapes.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

